{{Path|/etc/portage/package.mask}} is a file, or a directory of files, that can be used to prevent certain packages from being installed.

== Format ==

* One <var>DEPEND</var> atom per line; comment lines begin with a <code>#</code> (hash).
* For <var>DEPEND</var> atom syntax, see [[version specifier]].

== Example ==

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/package.mask]]|title=package.mask example|1=
# Mask beta versions greater than 1.97 of powertop since they have less features
>=sys-power/powertop-1.97

# Prevent MySQL from installing by masking the package (use MariaDB)
dev-db/mysql

# Want to go without Java 7; mask JDK and JRE that use Java 7.
virtual/jdk:1.7
virtual/jre:1.7
}}

